description:
Consumers should be able to send GET and PUT requests to the StoredProcedure that accesses
	the DigitalWeb SQL Database in order to retrieve prospect records or to insert/update prospect records.
name: Testing for Service

elements.description:
This scenario tests for whether the data was successfully inserted into the database for the first time
	and a formInstanceKey was generated and returned.
elements.name: Insert the form data into the database.

steps.name: that the formInstanceKey is 0 and formId is "aio-est" and formData is '[{ "field": "First Name", "value": "Waru" }, { "field": "Email Address", "value": "waru@example.com" }, { "field": "Last Name", "value": "W" }, { "field": "Phone", "value": "555-555-5555" }, { "field": "Zip Code", "value": "94530" }, { "field": "Company", "value": "First Republic" }]'
the microservice is invoked, the inputs should be passed into the StoredProc to write into the DB and return the formInstanceKey

elements.description:
This scenario tests for whether the data was successfully updated in the database
	and a formInstanceKey was returned.
elements.name: Update the form data in the database.

steps.name: that the formInstanceKey is 1 and formId is "" and formData is '[{ "field": "First Name", "value": "Maru" }, { "field": "Email Address", "value": "maru@example.com" }, { "field": "Last Name", "value": "M" }, { "field": "Phone", "value": "555-555-5555" }, { "field": "Zip Code", "value": "94530" }, { "field": "Country", "value": "Japan" }]'
the microservice is invoked, the inputs should be passed into the StoredProc to up into the DB and return the formInstanceKey

elements.description:
This scenario tests for whether the data was successfully updated into the database
	and a formInstanceKey was returned.
elements.name: Failed to update form because of bad formInstanceKey

steps.name: that the formInstanceKey is 443 and formId is "" and formData is '[{ "field": "Phone", "value": "555-555-5555" }, { "field": "Zip Code", "value": "94530" }, { "field": "Country", "value": "Japan" }]'
the microservice is invoked, the inputs should be passed into the StoredProc to update into the DB and return the formInstanceKey. But invalid formInstanceKey

elements.description:
This scenario tests for whether the data was successfully updated into the database
	and a formInstanceKey was returned.
elements.name: Failed to insert to database

steps.name: that the formInstanceKey is 0 and formId is "aio-est" and formData is '[]'
the microservice is invoked, the inputs should be passed into the StoredProc to insert into the DB and return the formInstanceKey. But no form data was given

elements.description:
This scenario tests for whether the data was successfully updated into the database
	and a formInstanceKey was returned.
elements.name: Failed to insert to database

This scenario tests for whether the data was successfully updated into the database

steps.name: that the formInstanceKey is 0 and formId is "" and formData is '[{ "field": "Country", "value": "Japan" }]'
